\id NAM Matupi Chin Standard Bible 
\h NAHUM 
\toc1 NAHUM 
\toc2 Nahum 
\toc3 Nah 
\mt1 NAHUM  
\mt2 (The Book of Nahum)  
\is1 Introduction  
\im Nahum dongah Boeipa loh pilnam a bom vetih Assyria ne Nineveh te a phae pa ni a ti. 721 \sc b.c.\sc*, vaengah Assyria caem loh tlangpuei Israel ram te a loh tih pilnam boeih te khohla la a om sak. Te Pathen loh pilnam te Assyria ukknah khui lamloh a hlawt vetih boethae rhalmah loh Israel te muk voel mahpawh. Nahum cabu he Hebrew rhoek loh hlohlai aka dung koek la a thui. Pathen kah thaomah neh Nineveh a bawtnah te tingtoenglung la a sak. Nahum cabu he 612 \sc b.c\sc* vaengah a tael coini a ti.  
\iot Outline  
\io1 I. An ode to God’s majesty \ior 1. 1—2. 2\ior*  
\io2 A. Superscription \ior 1. 1\ior*  
\io2 B. God’s vengeance \ior 1. 2-11\ior*  
\io2 C. Judah’s restoration \ior 1. 12—2. 2\ior*  
\io1 II. An ode on Nineveh’s destruction \ior 2. 3—3. 19\ior*  
\io2 A. The prophecy of Nineveh’s fall \ior 2. 3-13\ior*  
\io2 B. The cause of Nineveh’s fall \ior 3. 1-19\ior*  
\c 1  
\p
